    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-09T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-09T04:00:00-05:00" n="35"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d35">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/924</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-09T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 9, 4.45 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MCK1">Moser</persName> requests authorization <persName
                        corresp="#p_DLCWS1">Drysdale</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d35fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_DLCWS1">Lieut. Col. W. S. Drysdale</persName>,
                        Military Attaché at Peking.</note> proceed Siberia to gather the information
                    on conditions there as requested your instructions to him. Please instruct
                        <persName corresp="#p_MCK1">Moser</persName> directly.</p>
                <p>Naval attaché suggests advisability of sending to assist <persName
                        corresp="#p_DLCWS1">Drysdale</persName> a Serbian Colonel
                        <persName>Speskov</persName>, now here, available, who has offered his
                    services and is thoroughly familiar with the situation, speaking all necessary
                    languages. Please instruct me whether this and necessary expenses are
                    authorized.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RPS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
